What is the up to date way of configuring VSCode when using React.js within .jsx files? The strategies seem to keep changing over time with each release and since 0.10.8 my I continuously get errors with eslint and enabling the salsa preview stuff which seemed to work somewhat nicely in the insider preview doesn't seem to work at all. Since following bits of advice which include jsconfig.json, tsconfig.json, eslint plugins and configuration, and preview Salsa support it's hard to tell if I'm doing things the _current_ right way as of the latest release (0.10.8). If there are instructions somewhere layout what to do and perhaps what to _undo_ according to older guidance it would be helpful.

Examples of the errors I'm seeing in .jsx files.

``` jsx
// MyComponent.jsx
import React from 'react';
```

> Cannot compile modules unless the '--module' flag is provided. Consider setting the 'module' compiler option in a 'tsconfig.json' file.

``` js
// myFunction.js
export default function myFunction(options, key, env) {
```

> Cannot compile modules unless the '--module' flag is provided. Consider setting the 'module' compiler option in a 'tsconfig.json' file.
> function myFunction(options: any, key: any, env: any): any

``` jsx
// MyExport.jsx
export default MyExport;
```

> 'export=' can only be used in a .ts file.
> import reduxForm

Some files have identical imports or other syntax that get's no squigglys and others do without any apparent pattern.

